			<a name="q"></a>
			<h2>What are courses?</h2>
			<p>Courses are online classes on a specific topic. Courses may involve reading, watching videos, watching live conferences, or taking part in assignments by writing or uploading files. The AIM Participant Portal has a wide range of courses, from College Prep to French!</p>

			<a name="q2"></a>
			<h2>How do I start courses?</h2>
			<p>First find a course you would like to take - you can do this by clicking on "Courses" in the menu. You can then either browse through the course catalogue by looking into the categories on the left, or using the search in the menu bar to find the topic you want to learn about. <br><br>

			Click on a course to view it. You can then click on "Start Course" to start the course. Your started courses can be found in the "My Courses" page in the Courses section.</p>

			<a name="q3"></a>
			<h2>How do I finish courses?</h2>
			<p>To finish a course, you must first finish all the lessons in the course. If a course has 5 lessons, you'll need to mark the 5 lessons as complete before you can complete the course.<br><br>

			Once you have completed all the lessons, go to the lessons list page for the course, and click the "Complete Course" button at the bottom of the list.</p>

			<a name="q4"></a>
			<h2>What are lessons?</h2>
			<p>Lessons are parts of a course. They hold the content of the course, and have things like text, videos and assignments you can learn from.</p>

			<a name="q5"></a>
			<h2>How do I start lessons?</h2>
			<p>All lessons will become available to you once you start the course. To start a lesson after staring a course, go to the course in your "My Courses" page, and click "Start" on a lesson you would like to start.</p>

			<a name="q6"></a>
			<h2>How do I finish lessons?</h2>
			<p>To complete a lesson, scroll down to the bottom of the lesson you would like to complete, and click "Complete Lesson".</p>

			<a name="q7"></a>
			<h2>How do get some help with my lessons?</h2>
			<p>To get help from an instructor, you can either post in the forum, or use the contact form.<br><br>

				If you would like to make a public post about your question, you can go to the Forum and create a thread. The thread can be seen and replied to by other students and instructors.<br><br>

			If you would like to send a question in private, you can use the contact form.</p>

			<a name="q4"></a>
			<h2>What's the forum?</h2>
			<p>The forum is a place you can talk about your lessons.<br><br>

				To post in the forum, you must first create a profile - this just involves setting your user avatar from a selection of colors and shapes. The username for your profile will be your first name with 4 numbers after it. Your forum profile is set my the Participant Portal and cannot be changed.<br><br>

				After creating a forum profile, you are free to post new threads or reply to existing threads.
